definitions.definition: Innate , inherent , inseparable from the thing itself, essential .
examples: the intrinsic value of gold or silver
the intrinsic merit of an action

definitions.definition: Situated, produced, secreted in, or coming from inside an organ , tissue , muscle or member .

definitions.label_groups: programming , of a function or operator

main_definition: Innate , inherent , inseparable from the thing itself, essential .
